	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_65021973"><p>TP-Link should have been banned a long time ago, so yes it is quite late.  The reality though is that getting back that dominant market position requires significant time and resources, and until you have the large install base the scale of the security risk is limited.  Similar measures should be made for other Chinese brands.  Of course it is better to do it based on a security audit rather than nationality, but that is a little harder to implement.</p></div>
	</div>

