	<div class="commentBody">
		<div id="comment_body_65022645"><p>Attribution is practically impossible.  If there is a security hole (intentional or not), anyone can use it.  The only way to be sure who did it is if it was yourself.  Or if you catch them in the act at their own machine.</p><p>That's from a technical point of view.  From a political point of view, you can always attribute it to whoever it is most beneficial to you for them to have done it.  (Which can be embarrassing if the foreign state actors du jour turn out to have been a bored teenager in California again.)</p></div>
